			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I play a low level wood elf druid on Rallos.. Kelethin has got to the one of the worst &quot;I think I'm cool - lets get a high damage weapon and kill all the newbies&quot; zones. I made a druid solely for defense purposes although I've found that at level 1-5, just about anyone call kill you, regardless of your invis, gate, root, etc. I've also found that running to the guards does no good whatsoever. The immature PKers like to do the thing where they run back and forth with autoattack, hitting you, and as long as they keep moving the guards won't kill them. Same thing qualifies in the city, so even if I take the lift, they run around and kill me right up there. So what I've found to work (and be extremely humorous) when you're being attacked in a city is to wait for the attacker to get you down to about 2 bubs and just when they think they're going to kill you and steal your 5 silver 7 copper and maybe your *Worn Green Tunic, cast burst of flame on a merchant. They'll run over and smack you down right there. You don't lose faction and the PKer gets very irritated.   Amusing way to save yourself from a shameful death :P<BR>
<BR>
Anistasia Iceravyn - 46 Shaman of Rathe<BR>
Raelene - 7 Necro and Tashim - 5 Druid of Rallos Zek  hehe
