			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				One thing that I didn't see mentioned, or I missed it, is auto-run. If you are being attacked by someone who can't root you or stop you, click the Num Lock button. You can auto run forward as fast as you can go. Keep jumping and strafing left or right. Also type /y or go to guards. Once you hit Num Lock button you don't need the push the forward key and you can strafe easier and type.  One other tip to avoid being PK'd. If you are a class that can Hide, whenever you aren't moving....Hide. This is important if you are memming spells, or other things..resting up. This has been very important to my Dark Elf Necromancer. I get a big group of Dark Elves. Have them all Hide but one. A lightie comes up to you(of higher level) and starts attacking. The other people move and stop Hiding and the lighty panics. It is great fun to see someone who thinks they will kill you realize they rae going to die. Hope these help a little bit. <BR>
<BR>
Kill a lighty for me!<BR>
<BR>
-Nyneve
